%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20woman%20gave%202%20weeks'%20notice%20but%20was%20fired%20on%20the%20spot.%20Employment%20lawyers%20say%20it's%20not%20ethical%2C%20but%20it%20is%20legal.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222120%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20carrying%20a%20box%20of%20her%20belongings%20out%20of%20the%20office%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b0ebe4393cd3c8629b4b0d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEmployers%20can%20fire%20staff%20for%20any%20reason%20in%20most%20US%20states.%3Cp%3Efotostorm%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20woman%20was%20terminated%20immediately%20after%20giving%20her%20two%20weeks'%20notice.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20shared%20her%20story%20on%20TikTok%2C%20where%20people%20were%20shocked%20and%20suggested%20she%20sue%20her%20former%20company.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELegal%20experts%20said%20the%20company's%20actions%20were%20lawful%20but%20showed%20poor%20communication.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20woman%20who%20said%20she%20would%20be%20handing%20in%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-write-a-resignation-letter-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo%20weeks'%20notice%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20work%20was%20shocked%20when%20her%20company%20terminated%20her%20employment%20immediately%20without%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelsi%20posted%20a%20recording%20of%20a%20recent%20call%20she%20had%20with%20her%20employer%20on%20TikTok%20after%20she%20told%20her%20team%20lead%20she%20planned%20on%20leaving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20would%20give%20her%20two%20weeks'%20notice%20when%20she%20was%20ready.%20As%20far%20as%20Kelsi%20understood%20it%2C%20this%20was%20all%20agreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20she%20took%20a%20call%20to%20give%20the%20notice%2C%20her%20employer%20told%20her%20she%20would%20be%20leaving%20that%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20employer%20said%20that%20whenever%20someone%20on%20Kelsi's%20team%20gives%20their%20notice%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20have%20to%20accept%20that%20immediately%2C%26quot%3B%20citing%20the%20%26quot%3Bsensitivity%26quot%3B%20of%20her%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelsi%20was%20unhappy%20with%20the%20decision%20because%20she%20had%20been%20counting%20on%20working%20and%20getting%20paid%20for%20another%20two%20weeks.%20She%20told%20the%20employer%20she%20had%20been%20informed%20she%20would%20be%20able%20to%20finish%20her%20two%20weeks%20when%20she%20put%20it%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20pissed%20because%20I%20have%20three%20kids%2C%20and%20I%20have%20bills%20to%20pay%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelsi%20said%20in%20her%20video.%20%26quot%3BSo%20yes%2C%20I'm%20livid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelsi's%20video%20hit%20a%20nerve%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40heyitskelsi1%2Fvideo%2F7397170930524359966%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eamassing%201.6%20million%20views%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20comments%20were%20filled%20with%20people%20suggesting%20she%20hire%20an%20employment%20lawyer%20and%20claiming%20the%20company%20was%20turning%20her%20resignation%20into%20%26quot%3Bwrongful%20termination.%26quot%3B%20Kelsi%20did%20not%20reply%20to%20a%20request%20by%20Business%20Insider%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-prepare-what-say-layoff-termination-meeting-employment-lawyer-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegal%20experts%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20spoke%20with%20BI%20say%20the%20company%20was%20well%20within%20its%20rights.%20Whether%20it%20was%20ethical%2C%20though%2C%20is%20another%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d33c7298-8517-486a-83b9-31f57a82926b%5C%22%3EMost%20states%20follow%20'at%20will'%20employment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETom%20Spiggle%2C%20an%20employment%20law%20attorney%20based%20in%20Washington%20DC%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BFired%3F%20Afraid%20You%20Might%20Be%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI%20that%20this%20is%20when%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3Bat%20will%26quot%3B%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20quit%20at%20any%20time%2C%20and%20a%20company%20can%20terminate%20you%20at%20any%20time%20for%20any%20legal%20reason%2C%20even%20if%20you%20give%20advance%20notice%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpiggle%20added%20that%20there%20may%20be%20reasons%20a%20company%20would%20want%20to%20separate%20immediately%2C%20such%20as%20suspicions%20that%20the%20employee%20will%20take%20sensitive%20information.%20But%20there%20was%20no%20evidence%20of%20that%20happening%20in%20this%20particular%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ethical%20move%20would%20be%20to%20pay%20out%20the%20two%20weeks%2C%20even%20if%20the%20company%20wants%20to%20separate%20immediately%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJessica%20B.%20Summers%2C%20principal%20employment%20and%20labor%20attorney%20at%20Lerch%2C%20Early%2C%20%26amp%3B%20Brewer%2C%20told%20BI%20nobody%20was%20technically%20in%20the%20wrong%20in%20this%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20states%20in%20the%20US%20are%20%26quot%3Bat%20will%26quot%3B%20employment%20states%2C%20apart%20from%20Montana%2C%20meaning%20work%20contracts%20can%20end%20for%20any%20reason%20at%20any%20time.%20The%20only%20exception%20is%20when%20it%20is%20suspected%20the%20termination%20violates%20another%20law%20or%20public%20policy%2C%20such%20as%20being%20discriminatory%20or%20retaliatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20when%20an%20employee%20says%20they%20are%20leaving%2C%20absent%20a%20contract%2C%20the%20employee%20does%20have%20the%20legal%20right%20to%20end%20the%20relationship%20before%20the%20last%20day%20proposed%20by%20the%20employee%2C%26quot%3B%20Summers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Zelman%2C%20a%20labor%20and%20employment%20attorney%20in%20Berger%20Singerman's%20Fort%20Lauderdale%20office%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20if%20a%20company%20expects%20their%20employees%20to%20give%20the%20courtesy%20of%20a%20notice%20period%2C%20they%20should%20follow%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20an%20ethical%20standpoint%2C%20the%20company's%20treatment%20is%20unfair%20and%20likely%20disincentivizes%20other%20employees%20from%20providing%20the%20two-week%20courtesy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e475805e-9bfd-40df-bc18-22a9c38b9ab9%5C%22%3EPoor%20communication%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESummers%20said%20Kelsi's%20situation%20could%20have%20been%20vastly%20improved%20by%20better%20communication%20all%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20happened%20here%20was%20not%20a%20matter%20of%20anybody%20violating%20the%20law%20but%20rather%20poor%20communication%20across%20the%20board%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20Kelsi's%20supervisor%20was%20wrong%20for%20telling%20her%20she%20could%20work%20out%20her%20two%20weeks%20before%20checking%20with%20HR%20or%20someone%20with%20authority%20to%20make%20that%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESummers%20said%20this%20is%20a%20good%20reminder%20for%20employers%20to%20ensure%20that%20all%20supervisors%20and%20managers%20understand%20their%20authority%20and%20are%20well-trained%20in%20consulting%20the%20right%20people%20when%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20TikTok%20video%20exemplifies%2C%20a%20supervisor%20providing%20a%20wrong%20answer%20when%20they%20are%20placed%20on%20the%20spot%20can%20be%20much%20more%20damaging%20than%20simply%20letting%20the%20employee%20know%20that%20the%20supervisor%20doesn't%20know%20the%20answer%20or%20doesn't%20have%20the%20authority%20to%20make%20that%20call%2C%26quot%3B%20Summers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelsi%20said%20in%20the%20caption%20of%20her%20video%20that%20nobody%20should%20give%20any%20job%20the%20courtesy%20of%20a%20two-week%20notice%20because%20%26quot%3Bthis%20is%20the%20bullshit%20they%20will%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Hinton%20Westover%2C%20the%20chair%20and%20professor%20of%20organizational%20leadership%20and%20change%20at%20Utah%20Valley%20University%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20thought%20firing%20Kelsi%20this%20way%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20slimy%20thing%20for%20a%20company%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20why%20I%20always%20recommend%20to%20people%20to%20not%20give%20two-weeks%20notice%20anymore%2C%20as%20this%20is%20becoming%20more%20and%20more%20common%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2254be7a45-232a-440c-af4f-f00b840c89ca%5C%22%3EKnowing%20your%20rights%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKelsi's%20situation%20brings%20up%20another%20important%20question%2C%20Summers%20said%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20the%20separation%20would%20be%20considered%20resignation%20or%20termination%20and%20whether%20Kelsi%20is%20then%20eligible%20for%20unemployment%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnemployment%20laws%20vary%20from%20state%20to%20state%2C%20but%20typically%2C%20employees%20are%20not%20eligible%20for%20unemployment%20if%20they%20resign%2C%26quot%3B%20Summers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelsi%20posted%20an%20update%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20later%2C%20saying%20she%20had%20filed%20for%20unemployment%2C%20as%20she%20wasn't%20getting%20paid%20for%20the%20two%20weeks%20she%20would%20have%20worked.%20She%20said%20in%20the%20video%20she%20knew%20the%20employer%20acted%20legally%2C%20but%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bjust%20really%20freaking%20annoyed%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJanice%20Killion%2C%20an%20employment%20attorney%20at%20the%20firm%20JustAnswer%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20most%20employers%20appreciate%20notice%20prior%20to%20resignation%20because%20it%20gives%20them%20time%20to%20try%20to%20fill%20the%20position.%20However%2C%20workers%20should%20be%20aware%20of%20the%20risks%20they%20are%20taking%20by%20doing%20so%20and%20familiarize%20themselves%20with%20both%20their%20state's%20laws%20and%20their%20company's%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20in%20the%20employee's%20best%20interest%20when%20considering%20resignation%20to%20learn%20of%20the%20employer's%20past%20practice%20and%20to%20read%20the%20written%20employee%20policies%2C%26quot%3B%20Killion%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20may%20not%20guarantee%20continued%20employment%20during%20the%20notice%20period%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20can%20help%20inform%20the%20employee's%20decision-making%20and%20preparation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-a-company-may-terminate-you-after-giving-notice-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723204005000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b0ee46a5247369a3e97a1d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-a-company-may-terminate-you-after-giving-notice-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20woman%20recorded%20a%20conversation%20with%20her%20employer%20after%20giving%20her%20two%20weeks'%20notice%2C%20because%20she%20was%20shocked%20she%20was%20terminated%20immediately.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ldodgson%40insider.com%20(Lindsay%20Dodgson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-a-company-may-terminate-you-after-giving-notice-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Elite%20investor%20Jeremy%20Grantham%20warns%20stocks%20are%20poised%20to%20crash%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20recession%20seems%20inevitable%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222395%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22GettyImages%201193640564%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b5f361b4912df3ae1a317f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221197%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJeremy%20Grantham%20cofounded%20the%20asset%20management%20firm%20GMO.%3Cp%3EBoston%20Globe%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJeremy%20Grantham%20said%20stocks%20are%20dangerously%20expensive%20and%20a%20recession%20seems%20highly%20likely.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20bubble%20expert%20noted%20that%20past%20periods%20of%20lofty%20valuations%20were%20followed%20by%20painful%20downturns.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGrantham%20said%20he%20rang%20the%20alarm%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20too%20early%2C%20but%20that's%20nothing%20new%20for%20him.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI-fueled%20boom%20in%20stocks%20will%20end%20in%20catastrophe%20based%20on%20how%20past%20crazes%20have%20played%20out%2C%20and%20a%20recession%20looks%20assured%2C%20Jeremy%20Grantham%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20market%20there%20has%20ever%20been%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bubble%20historian%20and%20long-term%20investment%20strategist%20at%20GMO%20told%20the%20%26quot%3BWe%20Study%20Billionaires%26quot%3B%20podcast%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theinvestorspodcast.com%2Fepisodes%2Fstock-market-bubbles-ai-climate-change-jeremy-grantham%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eepisode%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrantham%20underscored%20that%20periods%20of%20steep%20price-to-earnings%20multiples%20on%20stocks%20are%20consistently%20followed%20by%20painful%20downturns.%20He%20pointed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-crash-1929-prediction-sp500-outlook-overvalued-john-hussman-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20veteran%20investor%20John%20Hussman%20showing%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20had%20surged%20this%20year%20to%20its%20most%20aggressive%20valuation%20since%201929.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20should%20give%20you%20cause%20for%20some%20concern%20and%20some%20caution%2C%20and%20of%20course%20the%20market%20does%20not%20feel%20concerned%20or%20cautious%2C%26quot%3B%20Grantham%20said%2C%20speaking%20before%20stocks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-